{"title": "Battle of Northern and Eastern Henan\n", "url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Battle_of_Northern_and_Eastern_Henan", "tags": ["Category:1938 in China", "Category:1938 in Japan", "Category:Battles of the Second Sino-Japanese War", "Category:Conflicts in 1938", "Category:History of Henan"], "text": "During the Second Sino-Japanese War the Japanese 1st Army under Lt. General Kiyoshi Katsuki drove the Chinese forces of General Cheng Qian's 1st War Area out of Northern and Eastern Honan until they were stopped by the disastrous 1938 Yellow River flood caused by the diversion of the Yellow River by the Chinese Army into the Chia-lu and Huai Rivers.\n\nOrder of battle\nFurther reading\nHsu Long-hsuen and Chang Ming-kai, History of The Sino-Japanese War (1937\u20131945) 2nd Ed., 1971. Translated by Wen Ha-hsiung, Chung Wu Publishing, pp. 230\u2013235. Map 9-2."}